summary: Masks in Context There is no shame in masks. In the hands of the dispossessed and marginalized they are powerful tools for...
caption:
Masks in Context

There is no shame in masks. In the hands of the dispossessed and marginalized they are powerful tools for survival and resistance. 

They protect individuals and they protect communities.

This is why activists with more privilege need to think in terms of masks, because they’re always going to be putting themselves at a relatively lesser risk of danger than those closest to them who are more marginalized.

So how do you know when it is time to mask up and when it is time to show the naked, loving ferocity of your face?

Look out for your own well-being first. Don’t make yourself a foolish martyr. I know you’re angry and just want these things to stop happening, but it’s a marathon, not a sprint. Your life is also part of the lives of those who know and love you.

Then, if you’re truly concerned for your loved ones, friends, neighbours, and accomplices, do the right thing and have a conversation with them about it.

What are their own concerns, boundaries, and fears? Listen to them.

I don’t believe in Batman’s mask. I only believe in Peter Parker’s mask when he is poor. And I absolutely believe in the power of Miles Morales’ mask.

summary: I hope it's not too late for a spidersona !! I just loved the movie so much I had to join 😂 Her superhero name is Armadeira...
body: I hope it’s not too late for a spidersona !! I just loved the movie so much I had to join 😂 Her superhero name is Armadeira (named after a venomous brazilian spider)!! I didn’t think of any special powers yet except for maybe venomous hands or webs? Idk I’ll work on it but I had a lot of fun designing her anyway!! Her outfit does glow in the dark which can be inconvenient but it’s also very good for intimidating people so 🤷🏾
